parameter.name: Memory Type
parameter.desc: Select the type of memory interface/types. Please refer to the TRM for a detailed list of supported memory controllers for Zynq family

parameter.name: Enable DDR
parameter.desc: Enable DDR Controller of Zynq PS

parameter.name: ECC
parameter.desc: ECC is supported only for data width of 16-bit

parameter.name: DRAM bus width
parameter.desc: Select the desired data width. Refer to the Thechnical Reference Manual(TRM) for a detailed list of supported DDR data widths

parameter.name: BURST Length (lppdr only)
parameter.desc: Select the burst Length. It refers to the amount of data read/written after a read/write command is presented to the controller

parameter.name: HIGH temperature
parameter.desc: Select the operating temparature

parameter.name: DRAM IC bus width
parameter.desc: Provide the width of the DRAM chip

parameter.name: Speed Bin
parameter.desc: Provide the Speed Bin

parameter.name: Operating Frequency (MHz)
parameter.desc: Chose the clock period for the desired frequency. The allowed freq range (200 - 667 MHz) is a function of FPGA part and FPGA speed grade

parameter.name: Operating Frequency (MHz)
parameter.desc: Chose the clock period for the desired frequency. The allowed freq range (200 - 667 MHz) is a function of FPGA part and FPGA speed grade

parameter.name: BANK Address Count
parameter.desc: Defines the bank to which an active an ACTIVE, READ, WRITE, or Precharge Command is being applied

parameter.name: ROW Address Count
parameter.desc: Provide the Row address for ACTIVE commands

parameter.name: COLUMN Address Count
parameter.desc: Provide the Row address for READ/WRITE commands

parameter.name: CAS Latency
parameter.desc: Select the Column Access Strobe (CAS) Latency. It refers to the amount of time it takes for data to appear on the pins of the memory module

parameter.name: CAS Write Latency
parameter.desc: Select the CAS Write Latency

parameter.name: RAS to CAS Delay
parameter.desc: Provide the row address to column address delay time. tRCD is t he time required between the memory controller asserting a row address strobe (RAS), and then asserting the column address strobe (CAS)

parameter.name: RECHARGE Time
parameter.desc: Precharge Time (tRP) is the number of clock cycles needed o terminate acces s to an open row of memory, and open access to the next row

parameter.name: tRC (ns )
parameter.desc: Provide the Row cycle time tRC (ns)

parameter.name: tRASmin ( ns )
parameter.desc: tRASmin (ns) is the minimum number of clock cycles required between an Active command and issuing the Precharge command

parameter.name: tFAW
parameter.desc: It restricts the number of activates that can be done within a certain window of time

parameter.name: ADDITIVE Latency
parameter.desc: Provide the Additive Latency (ns). Increases the efficiency of the command and data bus for sustainable bandwidths

parameter.name: DQS to Clock delay [0] (ns)
parameter.desc: The daly difference of each DQS path delay subtracted from the clock path delay

parameter.name: DQS to Clock delay [1] (ns)
parameter.desc: The daly difference of each DQS path delay subtracted from the clock path delay

parameter.name: DQS to Clock delay [2] (ns)
parameter.desc: The daly difference of each DQS path delay subtracted from the clock path delay

parameter.name: DQS to Clock delay [3] (ns)
parameter.desc: The daly difference of each DQS path delay subtracted from the clock path delay

parameter.name: Max freq of Device
parameter.desc: Select the desired memory part. For unlisted parts choose "Custom". This will enable user changes in the "Memory Part Configuration" section

parameter.name: Board delay [0] (ns)
parameter.desc: The average of the data midpoint delay, of the data delays associated with a byte lane (DDR_DQ, DDR_DM) averaged with the midpoint of the cloc kdelays (DDR_CK, DR_CK_N)

parameter.name: Board delay [1] (ns)
parameter.desc: The average of the data midpoint delay, of the data delays associated with a byte lane (DDR_DQ, DDR_DM) averaged with the midpoint of the cloc kdelays (DDR_CK, DR_CK_N)

parameter.name: Board delay [2] (ns)
parameter.desc: The average of the data midpoint delay, of the data delays associated with a byte lane (DDR_DQ, DDR_DM) averaged with the midpoint of the cloc kdelays (DDR_CK, DR_CK_N)

parameter.name: Board delay [3] (ns)
parameter.desc: The average of the data midpoint delay, of the data delays associated with a byte lane (DDR_DQ, DDR_DM) averaged with the midpoint of the cloc kdelays (DDR_CK, DR_CK_N)
